RainbruRPG::Core

RainbruRPG::Core Namespace Reference

Detailed Description

The namespace of the core classes.

The core classes are the managers, the templates and all the class that cannot be in another namespace. It provides a GameEngine/GameState mechanism : The GameState can have several GameState-based class (call gs????). Only one GameState can be on at a time and we can switch beetween them, pause and resume a GameState.

Enumeration Type Documentation

enum RainbruRPG::Core::tGameStateType

A GameState type used to change between state.

When we change the actual state, some states need extra initialization. The GameEngine can test its field to know from which state to which state we change.

Enumerator:
GST_MENU  The GameState is a menu.
GST_GAME  The GameState is game (with a map...).

enum RainbruRPG::Core::tVelocityType

Defines the translation type.

If defines how the velocity will change with the timeline.

Enumerator:
VT_INCREASE  The velocity increase with time.
VT_DECREASE  The velocity decrease with time.
VT_INC_DEC  The velocity Increase and then descrease.
VT_DEC_INC  The velocity first decrease then increase.
